<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-19221] IOException on log segment close shouldn&apos;t be ignored</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-19221</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Related to the findings in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-19200&quot; title=&quot;Indexes should be sanity checked on startup&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-19200&quot;&gt;KAFKA-19200&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;An IOException in &lt;tt&gt;TimeIndex#close&lt;/tt&gt; is currently silently ignored. This may potentially lead to a situation where &lt;tt&gt;TimeIndex#trimToValidSize&lt;/tt&gt; fails and the next broker startup will not attempt to recover the log segment as it considers the shutdown as &quot;clean&quot;, eventually causing the symptoms described in the aforementioned JIRA.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
